`,(0,k.jsx)(e.p,{children:"Not all business applications are appropriate for public blockchains. We've heard time and time again that while public retail chains give us amazing connectivity to the world, for regulated entities they come with challenges in compliance, privacy, and usability."}),`
`,(0,k.jsx)(e.p,{children:"These challenges differ based on jurisdiction and the type of entity, and it varies from use case to use case. What if there was a way to benefit from instant settlement, workflow efficiencies, and transaction auditability on a chain entirely catered to your use case?"}),`
`,(0,k.jsx)(e.h2,{children:"Private blockchains"}),`
`,(0,k.jsxs)(e.p,{children:["Over the last several years it's become easier for businesses and consortiums to use bespoke blockchains to solve these challenges. Traditional Enterprise Blockchain allows you to build on controlled private chains such as ",(0,k.jsx)(e.a,{href:"https://consensys.net/quorum/",children:"Quorum"}),", which is an open-source, permissioned version of the Ethereum blockchain, or ",(0,k.jsx)(e.a,{href:"https://www.hyperledger.org/use/fabric",children:"Hyperledger Fabric"}),", an open-source private distributed ledger. These solutions have been popular among very large enterprises."]}),`
